Subject: Inclusion: Multi-Sensory Room Drop-In (All Ages) Paul Palleschi Recreation Centre 9:30am - 11:30am
Description: Come out with your family and try out the new Multi-Sensory Room! The program will engage participants in sensory play working on fine and gross motor skills in the newly designed Multi-Sensory Room. The sensory room is a multi-sensory environment where participants can enjoy non-structured leisure activities. The room is equipped with lighting effects and tactile sensations that appeals to the senses.  Due to the duration length of this program, participants under ten (10) years of age do not need to be accompanied in the program.  However, parents/guardians are expected to remain at the program location for its duration in the event their immediate assistance is required.

Subject: Soccer (Turf) Daily Registration Drop-In (35+ Years) | Save Max Sports Centre 8:15-10:15pm
Description: An informal recreational, non-competitive game of soccer played on turf organized by those in attendance. Good behaviour guidelines must be adhered to.  Game play is intended for 8 vs 8 players.  Prerequisites: Pre-registration is required as well as producing valid photo id upon arrival. Pre-Registration is available 6 hours prior to drop-in start time.  All equipment will be provided, but participants are welcome to bring their own.     Required Equipment: Soccer ball, clean indoor soccer shoes/cleats.  Please be advised that we may request a physical photo identification (Drivers license/Government issue/School ID will be accepted) to verify participant ages and validate account information at check-in prior to program entry. This measure is implemented to ensure a positive and age-appropriate experience for all attendees.
Location: Save Max Sports Centre (Brampton Soccer Centre)
